.\" Man page for cbc - COIN-OR Branch and Cut MIP solver
.\" Generated from cbc --help topic metadata
.TH CBC 1 "April 2026" "CBC devel" "COIN-OR Utilities"
.SH NAME
cbc \- mixed-integer linear programming solver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cbc
.IR model.mps[.gz]
.RI [ options ]
.B \-solve
.br
.B cbc
.RI [ options ]
.B \-import
.I file
.B \-solve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cbc
is the COIN-OR Branch and Cut solver, an open-source mixed-integer
programming (MIP) solver.  It reads a model in MPS or LP format,
applies preprocessing, cut generation, and heuristics, then solves
via branch and bound.
.PP
Parameters must appear \fBbefore\fR \fB\-solve\fR to take effect.
Both single-dash (\fB\-sec\fR) and double-dash (\fB\-\-sec\fR) styles
are accepted.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B cbc model.mps \-solve
Solve with default settings.
.TP
.B cbc model.mps \-sec 300 \-solve
Solve with a 5-minute time limit.
.TP
.B cbc model.mps \-maxN 10000 \-ratio 0.01 \-solve
Stop after 10000 nodes or 1% gap.
.TP
.B cbc model.mps \-preprocess off \-solve
Disable integer preprocessing.
.TP
.B cbc model.mps \-cuts off \-solve
Disable all cut generators.
.TP
.B cbc model.mps \-heur off \-solve
Disable all primal heuristics.
.TP
.B cbc model.mps \-log 0 \-solve
Silent mode (no output).
.TP
.B cbc model.mps \-csvStatistics r.csv \-solve \-writeStatistics
Solve and append per-solve statistics to a CSV file.
.SH STOPPING CRITERIA
.TP
.BI \-sec " seconds"
Maximum wall-clock seconds (default: 1e8).
.TP
.BI \-maxN " nodes"
Maximum branch-and-bound nodes.
.TP
.BI \-maxSol " solutions"
Stop after finding this many feasible solutions.
.TP
.BI \-allow " gap"
Stop when absolute gap between best bound and incumbent < \fIgap\fR.
.TP
.BI \-ratio " fraction"
Stop when relative gap < \fIfraction\fR (e.g., 0.01 for 1%).
.TP
.BI \-cutoff " value"
All solutions must have objective better than \fIvalue\fR.
.SH CUT GENERATION
.TP
.BI \-cuts " mode"
Switch all cut generators on/off/root/ifmove/forceon.
.TP
.BI \-gomory " mode"
Gomory mixed-integer cuts.
.TP
.BI \-probing " mode"
Probing cuts.
.TP
.BI \-knapsack " mode"
Knapsack cover cuts.
.TP
.BI \-clique " mode"
Bron-Kerbosch clique cuts (requires conflict graph).
.TP
.BI \-oddwheel " mode"
Odd-wheel cuts (requires conflict graph).
.TP
.BI \-mir " mode"
Mixed-integer rounding cuts.
.TP
.BI \-flow " mode"
Flow cover cuts.
.TP
.BI \-twomir " mode"
Two-phase MIR cuts.
.TP
.BI \-zerohalf " mode"
Zero-half cuts.
.TP
.BI \-passCuts " n"
Number of cut passes at root node.
.TP
.BI \-passTreeCuts " n"
Number of cut passes in the tree.
.PP
Cut modes: \fBoff\fR, \fBon\fR, \fBroot\fR (root only),
\fBifmove\fR (if they improve bound), \fBforceon\fR.
.SH HEURISTICS
.TP
.BI \-heur " mode"
Switch most heuristics on/off.
.TP
.BI \-feas " mode"
Feasibility pump heuristic.
.TP
.BI \-round " mode"
Rounding heuristic.
.TP
.BI \-greedy " mode"
Greedy heuristic.
.TP
.BI \-Rins " mode"
Relaxation Induced Neighborhood Search.
.TP
.BI \-Rens " mode"
Relaxation Enforced Neighborhood Search.
.TP
.BI \-DivingC " mode"
Coefficient diving heuristic.
.TP
.BI \-combine " mode"
Combine solutions heuristic.
.PP
Heuristic modes: \fBoff\fR, \fBon\fR, \fBboth\fR, \fBbefore\fR.
.SH PREPROCESSING
.TP
.BI \-preprocess " mode"
Integer preprocessing (off/on/sos/equal/...).
.TP
.BI \-clqstr " mode"
Clique strengthening (off/after/before).
.TP
.BI \-cgraph " mode"
Conflict graph (on/off/clq).
.TP
.BI \-presolve " mode"
LP presolve (on/off/more).
.SH BRANCHING
.TP
.BI \-strong " n"
Number of variables for strong branching (default: 5).
.TP
.BI \-trust " n"
Branches before trusting pseudocosts (default: 10).
.TP
.BI \-node " strategy"
Node selection: hybrid/fewest/depth/upfewest/downfewest/updepth/downdepth.
.SH TOLERANCES
.TP
.BI \-integerT " tol"
Integer tolerance (default: 1e-6).
.TP
.BI \-increment " val"
Minimum improvement for a new solution (default: 1e-5).
.TP
.BI \-primalT " tol"
Primal feasibility tolerance.
.TP
.BI \-dualT " tol"
Dual feasibility tolerance.
.SH OUTPUT
.TP
.BI \-log " level"
Output verbosity: 0 (silent), 1 (default), 2+ (verbose).
.TP
.BI \-csvStatistics " file.csv"
Set CSV file for per-solve statistics.
.TP
.B \-writeStatistics
Append one row of statistics to the CSV file after solving.
.TP
.BI \-printMask " regex"
Only print solution variables matching \fIregex\fR.
.SH SOLVING
.TP
.B \-solve
Invoke branch and cut (required to start solving).
.TP
.B \-initialSolve
Solve LP relaxation only.
.TP
.BI \-threads " n"
Number of threads (each solve is single-threaded; used for deterministic parallel).
.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
When invoked without arguments or with \fB\-\fR, cbc enters interactive
mode.  Type \fB?\fR for a command list, \fB???\fR for all commands,
or \fIparam\fB??\fR for detailed help on a specific parameter.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B cbc
returns 0 on success.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR clp (1),
.BR glpsol (1)
.PP
